    {
      "id": "line-000",
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 6.48,
      "text": "This is a labor-vox recording. All labor-vox recordings are in the public domain.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 7.46,
      "end": 13.44,
      "text": "For more information or to volunteer, please visit laborvox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 14.66,
      "end": 16.98,
      "text": "Today's reading by Will McCoy.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 19.08,
      "end": 22.64,
      "text": "ASOP's Fables. The Trumpeter Taken Prisoner.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 23.56,
      "end": 32.56,
      "text": "A trumpeter marched into battle in the van of the army and put courage into his comrades by his warlike tunes.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 33.56,
      "end": 38.28,
      "text": "Being captured by the enemy, he begged for his life and said,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 39.28,
      "end": 47.32,
      "text": "Do not put me to death. I have killed no one. Indeed, I have no weapons, but carry with me only my trumpet here.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 48.38,
      "end": 53.74,
      "text": "But his captors replied, That is only the more reason why we should take your life.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 54.58,
      "end": 58.88,
      "text": "For though you do not fight yourself, you stir up others to do so.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 59.66,
      "end": 62.08,
      "text": "End of the trumpeter taken prisoner.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
